Management of non-profit organizations

>Too many leaders think that what they are doing and why they are doing it should be obvious to everyone.
> No such thing.
> I think everyone understood what many leaders said they did.
> But no one understands.
> ... To achieve results, you must spend time making yourself understood. P.30

What Leaders Should Do
>It is not charisma that is important.
> ... The first thing a leader should do is think through and define the [mission] of his or her organization. P.2

What is [mission]?
>What should be considered is what missions are valid (work) and what missions are not (don't work).
> ...The value of the mission is not in the beauty of the writing. It is in bringing about the right action (RIGHT ACTION). P.2

[It is essential for nonprofit leaders to consider the growth of their people].